in its efforts to support the Special Olympics was the first step in raising awareness.\n\n“It’s called ‘Cover the Cruiser,’” PPD Sergeant Aaron Jernigan said. “We’re just trying to get as many donations as we can for the Special Olympics. It just helps raise awareness for the Special Olympics. For those participating in it, all the participants and stuff like that.\n\n“It just helps make the event better for them whenever they go to participate.”\n\nThe next Law Enforcement Torch Run and Special Olympics will be held in 2025.\n\nWant more WDAM 7 news in your inbox? Clickhereto subscribe to our newsletter.\n\nCopyright 2024 WDAM. All rights reserved.", "title": "Petal Police 'Cover the Cruiser' for Special Olympics", "top-image": "https://gray-wdam-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/ZQUS7LH2HZBD3H7RCBSRRU6YEA.bmp?auth=a7ed9c54cffea7e6bf4cb35eb67dabb13660d057d63b3b8b84fea775be665a77&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "domain": "www.wdam.com", "lang": "en", "author": "", "description": "A Petal Police car got a makeover for a good cause.", "keywords": "Petal Police Department,Special Olympics,Cover the Cruiser"}